Some comments on b2

1. Probably a good idea to including compile instructions for rcerts with
the ripem sources--save digging up the ripem-dev message each time.

2. Even better to fix the makefile so you get it automatically, along with
some kind of message to make sure users copy it, as well as ripem to their
binary files.

3. Good idea to include the new IPRA certificate (CRL) in the standeard
issuers option of rcerts.

4. Probably a good idea to tell users how to change their file locations to
take account of the new ripem home directory and dropping of -P etc. A
little hand holding goes a long way in avoiding problems.

David
