The select a user capability of rcerts is extremely inconvenient to use. One
needs to know the exact format of the user name as the public key file
understands it.

1. Wild cards would be helpful. 

2. Even more helpful would be a select a user option to list all the users
in the public key file, one line per user, with a code before each (a letter
or two) which could then be used to select the user of interest.

David
